						               													<description>From the instructions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Use the exciting combination of scrambled letters, fast clues and definitions to find the original word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 1. Mix the cards up in each separate group&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 2. each players draws a card from the 4 letter word category&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 3. every player makes up a new work from the word they&amp;rsquo;ve picked&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 4. First player begins by telling everyone their newly created work&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 5. All other players must guess in 90 seconds what word first player originally picked&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 6. A clue will be given every 30 seconds&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 7. Record Points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step 8. Move to next player, then advance to next level&amp;#10;&amp;#10;---&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a nut shell there are 10 levels of cards 4 letters through 13 letters.  The object of the game is to use as many letters as possible on your clue card to make a new word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scoring is based on how many letters from the clue word are used in the new word, excluding any added letters and how quickly the word was guessed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every round all players play with words of the same length, advancing to longer words at the beginning of every new round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An example card:&amp;#10;4 letter&amp;#10;Knob : A small rounded handle&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
